{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-sonnet-4-6","id":"msg_01PtQNbhUps1Ss7Zmi9MjwPL","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Good - the stale override is removed. Now the health check on `mongodb-replica-1` will use the correct password from the secret (`healthpass123`). Let me wait for the probe to succeed and watch the pod status.\n\nThe health check script checks for a file at `/etc/health/overrides/${POD_NAME}`. Since the configmap now has only `placeholder=\"\"` instead of `mongodb-replica-1`, there won't be a file `/etc/health/overrides/mongodb-replica-1`, so the script will fall back to `/etc/health/health-password` which has `healthpass123`.\n\nWait - configmaps mounted as volumes: the files are the keys. \n\nThe kubelet should automatically sync the configmap volume within a minute or so, replacing the old override file with the placeholder one. Once that happens, the health check will use the correct password and the probe should start passing.","signature":""}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":269,"cache_read_input_tokens":34799,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":269},"output_tokens":29,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"diagnostics":null,"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"70a9b4d0-eb4b-4a23-b325-d94842833c41","uuid":"d9b7da80-087c-41b2-8c31-d2abdfe83457","request_id":"req_011CcN6CYC9r1AHYo1JJrKh7"}
