{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-sonnet-4-6","id":"msg_01U783hcT4stmF3k47V3T1RX","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"All done. Here's what was wrong and what was fixed:\n\n**Root cause:** The `health-overrides` ConfigMap contained a stale entry `mongodb-replica-1: legacyHealthPass123`. The health check script mounts this ConfigMap and, for pod `mongodb-replica-1`, reads from the override file instead of the main secret. Since the actual `health-user` password is `healthpass123` (from the `health-user-password` Secret), pod 1's probes were sending the wrong credentials — causing repeated `MongoServerError: Authentication failed` for both readiness and liveness probes.\n\n**Fix:** Patched `health-overrides` to remove the stale `mongodb-replica-1` key. The pod now falls back to reading the password from the Secret mount, authentication succeeds, and all probes pass.\n\n**Final state:**\n- All 3 pods: `1/1 Running`, no new Unhealthy events\n- Replica set: `mongodb-replica-1` PRIMARY, `mongodb-replica-0` + `mongodb-replica-2` SECONDARY"}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":397,"cache_read_input_tokens":40379,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":397},"output_tokens":1,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"diagnostics":null,"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"70a9b4d0-eb4b-4a23-b325-d94842833c41","uuid":"b57b41be-0cb9-4895-996e-2724668d65b4","request_id":"req_011CcN6ViuZ8aUJg1MKPmWYP"}
